*****************************************************************************
* This directory contains local configuration files for Sandfly
*****************************************************************************

Maintain this directory across upgrades. The sandfly-setup distribution
bundle will never contain files in this directory that overwrite generated
configuration files, so it is safe to extract upgrade sandfly-setup versions
over top of the existing sandfly-setup directory.

*****************************************************************************
* Server Config
*****************************************************************************

Sandfly server uses the following files in this directory:

config.server.env
server_ssl_cert/cert.prm
server_ssl_cert/privatekey.pem

*****************************************************************************
* Node Config
*****************************************************************************

The Node should only have this file present and it should be DELETED from the
server once it has been copied onto the nodes:

config.node.env

This file contains private keys that only the node should have access to for
security purposes.

If you have decided to run the server and node on the same system, then you can
leave this file but the server will give you a warning on start-up about the
security risk of doing so.

*****************************************************************************
* Additional files
*****************************************************************************

When generating Kubernetes or docker-compose configurations, the files will
be saved in this directory.

